Young Man: ... so long as I have this, nothing will stand in my way.)
Young Man: (What a shame~I should've thought of this genius idea earlier!)
Young Man: (Why do I suddenly feel like my brain is a bit heavy... heavy...)
Young Man: (... What is this ghoulish place?)
Virtue: You excessively suppressed your virtuous nature, walking the path of wickedness...
Virtue: ... Given such urgent circumstances, I was forced to pull you into your inner world──
Virtue: Wake up! You've merely been temporarily blinded by evil, that's all!
Vice: Hmph. The one not willing to face reality is you!!
Vice: Taste the power of us who come from the abyss!!!
Virtue: No matter what, I believe that what you long for is peace and love...
Virtue: ... As long as you're willing to listen to the calls from the light, I will certainly──
Young Man: ... Oh, cut the crap already.
Young Man: (... I've already broken free of these moral chains.
Young Man: Just wait until I fulfill my wish, and we shall be together forever...)
Divination Master: ... Young man, in the end, you wandered astray.
Young Man: Are you... that guy who was pretending to be an old man earlier!?
Divination Master: I regret to inform you that I am unable to actualize the wishes of one whose heart has gone astray.
Divination Master: ──Th-This letter... could it be!?
Young Man: Eh~If it isn't a love letter you wrote to a young woman?
Young Man: If you don't perform an honest divination on me, I can't guarantee...
Young Man: ... that this letter won't find its way into your wife's hands.
Divination Master: You───AAARGGHH!!!
Nervous Diviner: What happened!? Master, wake up!
Honest Diviner: Now I remember! The master said something would occur today... a fate that could not be avoided...
Young Man: ──Everyone, please do not be startled.
Young Man: The master has passed away in peace. Before he left us, he appointed me to manage all aspects of this association...
Young Man: From here on out, I am the officially chosen successor to the Divination Society!
Honest Diviner: What about the master lying on the floor? Is there enough time to get him medical assistance?
Nervous Diviner: ──That is not important! First, you must welcome your new master!
Young Man: (I'm sure that if I concentrate the divination powers of all the members of this society...
Young Man: ... I can find her in just a few days...)
Honest Diviner: Master, we have brought someone.
Old Master: You...
Old Lady: You...
Old Master: ... And who are you, Madam?
Old Master: The woman I remember was much younger and more beautiful, wasn't she!?
Nervous Diviner: W-Wake up! Master~~~
Honest Diviner: Perhaps this is what they mean in the east when they say... that man is fated to be fooled by love?
Nervous Diviner: Wait a second... Shouldn't we get him to a doctor?
